Since no one's said shit this morning...

There's no smut here, and no major conflict - only an Anon and his machine.
I've never been much for the racing genre games. Reading this was like visiting one of my parent's friends. The youngest son could beat anyone at the F-Zero games but me.
Racing shadowy unknowns is boring no matter how technically amazing the gameplay is. Shouting at each other is the gameplay.

Like that, there's nothing technically wrong here but there's also not an attempt to emphasize the challenge that could be.
I could see this as a three parter, where this is the first, the second as a Deadline race where Anon just barely survives due to the limiter and boost. That gives us a thrill as he has to get everything right again in the third part.

Or the reader could say fuck it.
Every race is about that race entirely.
Not the other racers, not the next, not the last one.
Go fast and pray your heart holds out.
